{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43091935-d11f-484e-ac4d-ea034451b78a","content":"**Exit code 8** in MTP means \"no tests were discovered.\" MTP treats this as a failure by default, unlike VSTest which silently passed.\n\n**Fix — add `--ignore-exit-code 8` to your CI pipeline:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --ignore-exit-code 8\n```\n\nOr set the environment variable (useful for CI globally):\n\n```bash\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8\ndotnet test\n```\n\n**Alternatively**, if you want to configure it at the project level so every `dotnet test` invocation is covered, add this to your `.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis tells MTP to return exit code 0 (success) when zero tests are found, restoring the VSTest behavior for your conditionally-compiled assemblies.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3756b7d5-a793-43bb-874d-a93cc82bf654","outputTokens":235,"requestId":"E853:1420E8:26E49C7:295DF4F:6A049413"},"id":"1c535db9-cb71-4365-bd13-dafba18f952d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:09:15.299Z","parentId":"2b65b4b2-9920-40e3-a430-4456c58c05c3"}
